I am writing because I am concerned about the future of the Burke County school system. I am a parent of a third grade student and registered voter from Burke County.  I grew up in Burke County and was educated in its school system.  I went on to graduate from UNC-Charlotte in 1991.  I could have lived anywhere; however, I decided to move back to Morganton because I wanted to raise a family in the same small town fashion I knew well.  I knew that Morganton was a safe, friendly and supportive community, with good schools and good teachers.  Unfortunately, that all seems to be changing right in front of my eyes.  I am sure you are aware of the issues that surround our current School Board and their decision to break Superintendent Burleson’s contract and let him go.  In brief, five of the elected School Board officials have caused a mockery of our school system and continue to defy common sense. 



