Not only that, but they voted to spend precious tax dollars on a Special Counsel to assess their legal dillemas against the Superintendent, the ACLU, the NAACP, the SACS-CASI, and God-knows who else.

Our county is suffering needlessly from the foolishness of Tim Buff, Tracy Norman, Rob Hairfield, and Karen Sain.  You all say this is a local issue, and you're right.  You say you are powerless to step in.  Maybe so.  But the State has taken away any opportunity to allow Burke's 89,000 citizens to clean up the mistake of the 5000 citizens who voted for this bunch.  Our county cannot sit through more-of-the-same -  thumbing their noses at the wishes of the people.  Yes.  Come November, because of the resignation of ONE of the five trouble-makers, this county WILL take back the majority of the board by electing decent people.  But in the meantime, our beloved Superintendent will be gone, students worried about the possibility of having to attend an unaccredited high school will be gone, and many of our teachers (due to budget cuts, attrition, and fear of board retaliation) will be gone.

Is that what you want?  We now have a 16.3% unemployment rate here in Burke.  What industry or company is going to bring their business to a place with unaccredited high schools?

At last night's meeting, all 2400 people were very orderly.  We had over 20 law enforcement people there to keep order, including our Sheriff and Public Safety Chief.  Given the gravity of the situation and the escalating impatience and anger of the citizenry, I am concerned that the order and the peace will become more difficult to maintain at each successive meeting.  As I am also a member of the Burke County BOE, I made the motion to rescind the April 20th vote on Mr. Burleson's contract and to extend that contract to June 30, 2010.  The motion died on a 3 - 3 tie.  I wanted to give them one more chance to right the wrongs this bunch have imposed on Burke County's school system, its students, and its economy.  They chose to stand firm and end David's employment on June 30, 2009.  They chose to jeopardize our accreditation.  They chose to continue to ruin Burke County's good-schools reputation.

I have served on the Burke County Board of Education for almost twelve years now.  Governor, I represent YOU, on the regional Teaching Fellows interview committee each year.  I'm proud of you, and, of course, I voted for you.  But please don't do me any favors.  Do what you can for our county, our schools, and our kids. Please.

You're all probably tired of hearing about the injustice here in Burke County, but you will continue to hear about it as long as we must endure this vendetta against our Superintendent, our citizens, and now against our students by these political thugs.  I cannot be more candid than that.

